g/college to feed and shelter myself as an adult!!! This former customer is now in charge of guiding my child to adulthood, why would I chose for them to spend years in a FAILING SYSTEM??? The yearly ritual of &quot;graduating&quot; young adults with a diploma that barely represents attendance is deplorable. There a few employers who accept this &quot;diploma&quot; anymore, secondary education to survive in this world in now mandatory! The utter failure of the public schools seems to parallel the POST OFFICE. Ironically, they are both run by CONGRESS!!!!! "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="849" language="en" documentId="2704" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="aerostar" date="Aug 29, 2013 8:26PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="6" thumbsDown="0" origId="2704" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="849"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>